  "text": "Upregulation of BCL-6 expression by GC precursor B cells seems to enhance integrin-dependent conjugation of B cells and T cells [CITATION_1] , which is a defining feature of their interaction [CITATION_2] . Finally, it is interesting to note that naive B cells express BCL6 mRNA in the absence of protein [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] , which suggests a role for post-transcriptional regulation of BCL-6 expression in B cells [CITATION_5] and T cells [CITATION_6] , perhaps allowing for the rapid upregulation of BCL-6 protein expression upon antigen activation.",
